thread.title: Nanny Accused of Murdering Two Children to Stand Trial

author: Corinne Ramey
title: Nanny Accused of Murdering Two Children to Stand Trial
text:
The New York City nanny accused of fatally stabbing her two young charges in 2012 is expected to go to trial as soon as this month, casting renewed light on an event that stunned an affluent Manhattan neighborhood and changed how some parents hire caretakers.
Yoselyn Ortega, 55 years old, is charged with two counts of first-degree murder and two counts of second-degree murder. She is in jail awaiting trial. Jury selection began earlier this month in Manhattan.
